  "log": null,
  "summary": "The issue reports incorrect matching semantics in Onigmo where escape sequences like \\w behave differently when used inside a character class (e.g. [\\w]) under combined ASCII and ignore-case flags ((?ia)). Specifically, character-class expansion and case-folding are applied beyond the ASCII range even when the ASCII flag is present, causing U+017F, U+212A, U+00DF, etc. to be matched incorrectly. This is a semantic bug (incorrect matching) observed in Onigmo 5.10.0–5.14.2 and in Ruby's bundled Oniguruma 5.9.x; the reporter found it by comparing behavior to Perl and running manual tests (differential testing). No fix or commit is mentioned in the issue or comments."
}

